151void _UI_Init( qboolean );
152void _UI_Shutdown( void );
153void _UI_KeyEvent( int key, qboolean down );
154void _UI_MouseEvent( int dx, int dy );
155void _UI_Refresh( int realtime );
156qboolean _UI_IsFullscreen( void );
157Q_EXPORT intptr_t vmMain( int command, int arg0, int arg1, int arg2, int arg3, int arg4, int arg5, int arg6, int arg7, int arg8, int arg9, int arg10, int arg11 ) {
158 switch ( command ) {
159 case UI_GETAPIVERSION:
160 return UI_API_VERSION;
161
162 case UI_INIT:
163 _UI_Init(arg0);
164 return 0;
165
166 case UI_SHUTDOWN:
167 _UI_Shutdown();
168 return 0;
169
170 case UI_KEY_EVENT:
171 _UI_KeyEvent( arg0, arg1 );
172 return 0;
173
174 case UI_MOUSE_EVENT:
175 _UI_MouseEvent( arg0, arg1 );
176 return 0;
177
178 case UI_REFRESH:
179 _UI_Refresh( arg0 );
180 return 0;
181
182 case UI_IS_FULLSCREEN:
183 return _UI_IsFullscreen();
184
185 case UI_SET_ACTIVE_MENU:
186 _UI_SetActiveMenu( arg0 );
187 return 0;
188
189 case UI_CONSOLE_COMMAND:
190 return UI_ConsoleCommand(arg0);
191
192 case UI_DRAW_CONNECT_SCREEN:
193 UI_DrawConnectScreen( arg0 );
194 return 0;
195 case UI_HASUNIQUECDKEY: // mod authors need to observe this
196 return qtrue; // change this to qfalse for mods!
197
198 }
199
200 return -1;
201}

265int Text_Width(const char *text, float scale, int limit) {
266 int count,len;
267 float out;
268 glyphInfo_t *glyph;
269 float useScale;
270 const char *s = text;
271 fontInfo_t *font = &uiInfo.uiDC.Assets.textFont;
272 if (scale <= ui_smallFont.value) {
273 font = &uiInfo.uiDC.Assets.smallFont;
274 } else if (scale >= ui_bigFont.value) {
275 font = &uiInfo.uiDC.Assets.bigFont;
276 }
277 useScale = scale * font->glyphScale;
278 out = 0;
279 if (text) {
280 len = strlen(text);
281 if (limit > 0 && len > limit) {
282 len = limit;
283 }
284 count = 0;
285 while (s && *s && count < len) {
286 if ( Q_IsColorString(s) ) {
287 s += 2;
288 continue;
289 } else {
290 glyph = &font->glyphs[*s & 255];
291 out += glyph->xSkip;
292 s++;
293 count++;
294 }
295 }
296 }
297 return out * useScale;
298}
299
300int Text_Height(const char *text, float scale, int limit) {
301 int len, count;
302 float max;
303 glyphInfo_t *glyph;
304 float useScale;
305 const char *s = text;
306 fontInfo_t *font = &uiInfo.uiDC.Assets.textFont;
307 if (scale <= ui_smallFont.value) {
308 font = &uiInfo.uiDC.Assets.smallFont;
309 } else if (scale >= ui_bigFont.value) {
310 font = &uiInfo.uiDC.Assets.bigFont;
311 }
312 useScale = scale * font->glyphScale;
313 max = 0;
314 if (text) {
315 len = strlen(text);
316 if (limit > 0 && len > limit) {
317 len = limit;
318 }
319 count = 0;
320 while (s && *s && count < len) {
321 if ( Q_IsColorString(s) ) {
322 s += 2;
323 continue;
324 } else {
325 glyph = &font->glyphs[*s & 255];
326 if (max < glyph->height) {
327 max = glyph->height;
328 }
329 s++;
330 count++;
331 }
332 }
333 }
334 return max * useScale;
335}

345void Text_Paint(float x, float y, float scale, vec4_t color, const char *text, float adjust, int limit, int style) {
346 int len, count;
347 vec4_t newColor;
348 glyphInfo_t *glyph;
349 float useScale;
350 fontInfo_t *font = &uiInfo.uiDC.Assets.textFont;
351 if (scale <= ui_smallFont.value) {
352 font = &uiInfo.uiDC.Assets.smallFont;
353 } else if (scale >= ui_bigFont.value) {
354 font = &uiInfo.uiDC.Assets.bigFont;
355 }
356 useScale = scale * font->glyphScale;
357 if (text) {
358 const char *s = text;
359 trap_R_SetColor( color );
360 memcpy(&newColor[0], &color[0], sizeof(vec4_t));
361 len = strlen(text);
362 if (limit > 0 && len > limit) {
363 len = limit;
364 }
365 count = 0;
366 while (s && *s && count < len) {
367 glyph = &font->glyphs[*s & 255];
368 //int yadj = Assets.textFont.glyphs[text[i]].bottom + Assets.textFont.glyphs[text[i]].top;
369 //float yadj = scale * (Assets.textFont.glyphs[text[i]].imageHeight - Assets.textFont.glyphs[text[i]].height);
370 if ( Q_IsColorString( s ) ) {
371 memcpy( newColor, g_color_table[ColorIndex(*(s+1))], sizeof( newColor ) );
372 newColor[3] = color[3];
373 trap_R_SetColor( newColor );
374 s += 2;
375 continue;
376 } else {
377 float yadj = useScale * glyph->top;
378 if (style == ITEM_TEXTSTYLE_SHADOWED || style == ITEM_TEXTSTYLE_SHADOWEDMORE) {
379 int ofs = style == ITEM_TEXTSTYLE_SHADOWED ? 1 : 2;
380 colorBlack[3] = newColor[3];
381 trap_R_SetColor( colorBlack );
382 Text_PaintChar(x + ofs, y - yadj + ofs,
383 glyph->imageWidth,
384 glyph->imageHeight,
385 useScale,
386 glyph->s,
387 glyph->t,
388 glyph->s2,
389 glyph->t2,
390 glyph->glyph);
391 trap_R_SetColor( newColor );
392 colorBlack[3] = 1.0;
393 }
394 Text_PaintChar(x, y - yadj,
395 glyph->imageWidth,
396 glyph->imageHeight,
397 useScale,
398 glyph->s,
399 glyph->t,
400 glyph->s2,
401 glyph->t2,
402 glyph->glyph);
403
404 x += (glyph->xSkip * useScale) + adjust;
405 s++;
406 count++;
407 }
408 }
409 trap_R_SetColor( NULL );
410 }
411}

413void Text_PaintWithCursor(float x, float y, float scale, vec4_t color, const char *text, int cursorPos, char cursor, int limit, int style) {
414 int len, count;
415 vec4_t newColor;
416 glyphInfo_t *glyph, *glyph2;
417 float yadj;
418 float useScale;
419 fontInfo_t *font = &uiInfo.uiDC.Assets.textFont;
420 if (scale <= ui_smallFont.value) {
421 font = &uiInfo.uiDC.Assets.smallFont;
422 } else if (scale >= ui_bigFont.value) {
423 font = &uiInfo.uiDC.Assets.bigFont;
424 }
425 useScale = scale * font->glyphScale;
426 if (text) {
427 const char *s = text;
428 trap_R_SetColor( color );
429 memcpy(&newColor[0], &color[0], sizeof(vec4_t));
430 len = strlen(text);
431 if (limit > 0 && len > limit) {
432 len = limit;
433 }
434 count = 0;
435 glyph2 = &font->glyphs[cursor & 255];
436 while (s && *s && count < len) {
437 glyph = &font->glyphs[*s & 255];
438 //int yadj = Assets.textFont.glyphs[text[i]].bottom + Assets.textFont.glyphs[text[i]].top;
439 //float yadj = scale * (Assets.textFont.glyphs[text[i]].imageHeight - Assets.textFont.glyphs[text[i]].height);
440 if ( Q_IsColorString( s ) ) {
441 memcpy( newColor, g_color_table[ColorIndex(*(s+1))], sizeof( newColor ) );
442 newColor[3] = color[3];
443 trap_R_SetColor( newColor );
444 s += 2;
445 continue;
446 } else {
447 yadj = useScale * glyph->top;
448 if (style == ITEM_TEXTSTYLE_SHADOWED || style == ITEM_TEXTSTYLE_SHADOWEDMORE) {
449 int ofs = style == ITEM_TEXTSTYLE_SHADOWED ? 1 : 2;
450 colorBlack[3] = newColor[3];
451 trap_R_SetColor( colorBlack );
452 Text_PaintChar(x + ofs, y - yadj + ofs,
453 glyph->imageWidth,
454 glyph->imageHeight,
455 useScale,
456 glyph->s,
457 glyph->t,
458 glyph->s2,
459 glyph->t2,
460 glyph->glyph);
461 colorBlack[3] = 1.0;
462 trap_R_SetColor( newColor );
463 }
464 Text_PaintChar(x, y - yadj,
465 glyph->imageWidth,
466 glyph->imageHeight,
467 useScale,
468 glyph->s,
469 glyph->t,
470 glyph->s2,
471 glyph->t2,
472 glyph->glyph);
473
474 yadj = useScale * glyph2->top;
475 if (count == cursorPos && !((uiInfo.uiDC.realTime/BLINK_DIVISOR) & 1)) {
476 Text_PaintChar(x, y - yadj,
477 glyph2->imageWidth,
478 glyph2->imageHeight,
479 useScale,
480 glyph2->s,
481 glyph2->t,
482 glyph2->s2,
483 glyph2->t2,
484 glyph2->glyph);
485 }
486
487 x += (glyph->xSkip * useScale);
488 s++;
489 count++;
490 }
491 }
492 // need to paint cursor at end of text
493 if (cursorPos == len && !((uiInfo.uiDC.realTime/BLINK_DIVISOR) & 1)) {
494 yadj = useScale * glyph2->top;
495 Text_PaintChar(x, y - yadj,
496 glyph2->imageWidth,
497 glyph2->imageHeight,
498 useScale,
499 glyph2->s,
500 glyph2->t,
501 glyph2->s2,
502 glyph2->t2,
503 glyph2->glyph);
504
505 }
506
507 trap_R_SetColor( NULL );
508 }
509}

512static void Text_Paint_Limit(float *maxX, float x, float y, float scale, vec4_t color, const char* text, float adjust, int limit) {
513 int len, count;
514 vec4_t newColor;
515 glyphInfo_t *glyph;
516 if (text) {
517 const char *s = text;
518 float max = *maxX;
519 float useScale;
520 fontInfo_t *font = &uiInfo.uiDC.Assets.textFont;
521 if (scale <= ui_smallFont.value) {
522 font = &uiInfo.uiDC.Assets.smallFont;
523 } else if (scale > ui_bigFont.value) {
524 font = &uiInfo.uiDC.Assets.bigFont;
525 }
526 useScale = scale * font->glyphScale;
527 trap_R_SetColor( color );
528 len = strlen(text);
529 if (limit > 0 && len > limit) {
530 len = limit;
531 }
532 count = 0;
533 while (s && *s && count < len) {
534 glyph = &font->glyphs[*s & 255];
535 if ( Q_IsColorString( s ) ) {
536 memcpy( newColor, g_color_table[ColorIndex(*(s+1))], sizeof( newColor ) );
537 newColor[3] = color[3];
538 trap_R_SetColor( newColor );
539 s += 2;
540 continue;
541 } else {
542 float yadj = useScale * glyph->top;
543 if (Text_Width(s, scale, 1) + x > max) {
544 *maxX = 0;
545 break;
546 }
547 Text_PaintChar(x, y - yadj,
548 glyph->imageWidth,
549 glyph->imageHeight,
550 useScale,
551 glyph->s,
552 glyph->t,
553 glyph->s2,
554 glyph->t2,
555 glyph->glyph);
556 x += (glyph->xSkip * useScale) + adjust;
557 *maxX = x;
558 count++;
559 s++;
560 }
561 }
562 trap_R_SetColor( NULL );
563 }

590#define UI_FPS_FRAMES 4
591void _UI_Refresh( int realtime )
592{
593 static int index;
594 static int previousTimes[UI_FPS_FRAMES];
595
596 //if ( !( trap_Key_GetCatcher() & KEYCATCH_UI ) ) {
597 // return;
598 //}
599
600 uiInfo.uiDC.frameTime = realtime - uiInfo.uiDC.realTime;
601 uiInfo.uiDC.realTime = realtime;
602
603 previousTimes[index % UI_FPS_FRAMES] = uiInfo.uiDC.frameTime;
604 index++;
605 if ( index > UI_FPS_FRAMES ) {
606 int i, total;
607 // average multiple frames together to smooth changes out a bit
608 total = 0;
609 for ( i = 0 ; i < UI_FPS_FRAMES ; i++ ) {
610 total += previousTimes[i];
611 }
612 if ( !total ) {
613 total = 1;
614 }
615 uiInfo.uiDC.FPS = 1000 * UI_FPS_FRAMES / total;
616 }
617
618
619
620 UI_UpdateCvars();
621
622 if (Menu_Count() > 0) {
623 // paint all the menus
624 Menu_PaintAll();
625 // refresh server browser list
626 UI_DoServerRefresh();
627 // refresh server status
628 UI_BuildServerStatus(qfalse);
629 // refresh find player list
630 UI_BuildFindPlayerList(qfalse);
631 }
632
633 // draw cursor
634 UI_SetColor( NULL );
635 if (Menu_Count() > 0 && (trap_Key_GetCatcher() & KEYCATCH_UI)) {
636 UI_DrawHandlePic( uiInfo.uiDC.cursorx-16, uiInfo.uiDC.cursory-16, 32, 32, uiInfo.uiDC.Assets.cursor);
637 }
638
639#ifndef NDEBUG
640 if (uiInfo.uiDC.debug)
641 {
642 // cursor coordinates
643 //FIXME
644 //UI_DrawString( 0, 0, va("(%d,%d)",uis.cursorx,uis.cursory), UI_LEFT|UI_SMALLFONT, colorRed );
645 }
646#endif
647
648}

660
661char *GetMenuBuffer(const char *filename) {
662 int len;
663 fileHandle_t f;
664 static char buf[MAX_MENUFILE];
665
666 len = trap_FS_FOpenFile( filename, &f, FS_READ );
667 if ( !f ) {
668 trap_Print( va( S_COLOR_RED "menu file not found: %s, using default\n", filename ) );
669 return defaultMenu;
670 }
671 if ( len >= MAX_MENUFILE ) {
672 trap_Print( va( S_COLOR_RED "menu file too large: %s is %i, max allowed is %i\n", filename, len, MAX_MENUFILE ) );
673 trap_FS_FCloseFile( f );
674 return defaultMenu;
675 }
676
677 trap_FS_Read( buf, len, f );
678 buf[len] = 0;
679 trap_FS_FCloseFile( f );
680 //COM_Compress(buf);
681 return buf;
682
683}

685qboolean Asset_Parse(int handle) {
686 pc_token_t token;
687 const char *tempStr;
688
689 if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token))
690 return qfalse;
691 if (Q_stricmp(token.string, "{") != 0) {
692 return qfalse;
693 }
694
695 while ( 1 ) {
696
697 memset(&token, 0, sizeof(pc_token_t));
698
699 if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token))
700 return qfalse;
701
702 if (Q_stricmp(token.string, "}") == 0) {
703 return qtrue;
704 }
705
706 // font
707 if (Q_stricmp(token.string, "font") == 0) {
708 int pointSize;
709 if (!PC_String_Parse(handle, &tempStr) || !PC_Int_Parse(handle,&pointSize)) {
710 return qfalse;
711 }
712 trap_R_RegisterFont(tempStr, pointSize, &uiInfo.uiDC.Assets.textFont);

851void UI_ParseMenu(const char *menuFile) {
852 int handle;
853 pc_token_t token;
854
855 Com_Printf("Parsing menu file: %s\n", menuFile);
856
857 handle = trap_PC_LoadSource(menuFile);
858 if (!handle) {
859 return;
860 }
861
862 while ( 1 ) {
863 memset(&token, 0, sizeof(pc_token_t));
864 if (!trap_PC_ReadToken( handle, &token )) {
865 break;
866 }
867
868 //if ( Q_stricmp( token, "{" ) ) {
869 // Com_Printf( "Missing { in menu file\n" );
870 // break;
871 //}
872
873 //if ( menuCount == MAX_MENUS ) {
874 // Com_Printf( "Too many menus!\n" );
875 // break;
876 //}
877
878 if ( token.string[0] == '}' ) {
879 break;
880 }
881
882 if (Q_stricmp(token.string, "assetGlobalDef") == 0) {
883 if (Asset_Parse(handle)) {
884 continue;
885 } else {
886 break;
887 }
888 }
889
890 if (Q_stricmp(token.string, "menudef") == 0) {
891 // start a new menu
892 Menu_New(handle);
893 }
894 }
895 trap_PC_FreeSource(handle);
896}
897
898qboolean Load_Menu(int handle) {
899 pc_token_t token;
900
901 if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token))
902 return qfalse;
903 if (token.string[0] != '{') {
904 return qfalse;
905 }
906
907 while ( 1 ) {
908
909 if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token))
910 return qfalse;
911
912 if ( token.string[0] == 0 ) {
913 return qfalse;
914 }
915
916 if ( token.string[0] == '}' ) {
917 return qtrue;
918 }
919
920 UI_ParseMenu(token.string);
921 }
922 return qfalse;
923}
924
925void UI_LoadMenus(const char *menuFile, qboolean reset) {
926 pc_token_t token;
927 int handle;
928 int start;
929
930 start = trap_Milliseconds();
931
932 handle = trap_PC_LoadSource( menuFile );
933 if (!handle) {
934 Com_Printf( S_COLOR_YELLOW "menu file not found: %s, using default\n", menuFile );
935 handle = trap_PC_LoadSource( "ui/menus.txt" );
936 if (!handle) {
937 trap_Error( S_COLOR_RED "default menu file not found: ui/menus.txt, unable to continue!" );
938 }
939 }
940
941 ui_new.integer = 1;
942
943 if (reset) {
944 Menu_Reset();
945 }
946
947 while ( 1 ) {
948 if (!trap_PC_ReadToken(handle, &token))
949 break;
950 if( token.string[0] == 0 || token.string[0] == '}') {
951 break;
952 }
953
954 if ( token.string[0] == '}' ) {
955 break;
956 }
957
958 if (Q_stricmp(token.string, "loadmenu") == 0) {
959 if (Load_Menu(handle)) {
960 continue;
961 } else {
962 break;
963 }
964 }
965 }
966
967 Com_Printf("UI menu load time = %d milli seconds\n", trap_Milliseconds() - start);
968
969 trap_PC_FreeSource( handle );
970}

972void UI_Load(void) {
973 char lastName[1024];
974 menuDef_t *menu = Menu_GetFocused();
975 char *menuSet = UI_Cvar_VariableString("ui_menuFiles");
976 if (menu && menu->window.name) {
977 Q_strncpyz(lastName, menu->window.name, sizeof(lastName));
978 }
979 if (menuSet == NULL || menuSet[0] == '\0') {
980 menuSet = "ui/menus.txt";
981 }
982
983 String_Init();
984
985#ifdef PRE_RELEASE_TADEMO
986 UI_ParseGameInfo("demogameinfo.txt");
987#else
988 UI_ParseGameInfo("gameinfo.txt");
989 UI_LoadArenas();
990#endif
991
992 UI_LoadMenus(menuSet, qtrue);
993 Menus_CloseAll();
994 Menus_ActivateByName(lastName);
995
996}

1635static int UI_OwnerDrawWidth(int ownerDraw, float scale) {
1636 int i, h, value;
1637 const char *text;
1638 const char *s = NULL;
1639
1640 switch (ownerDraw) {
1641 case UI_HANDICAP:
1642 h = Com_Clamp( 5, 100, trap_Cvar_VariableValue("handicap") );
1643 i = 20 - h / 5;
1644 s = handicapValues[i];
1645 break;
1646 case UI_CLANNAME:
1647 s = UI_Cvar_VariableString("ui_teamName");
1648 break;
1649 case UI_GAMETYPE:
1650 s = uiInfo.gameTypes[ui_gameType.integer].gameType;
1651 break;
1652 case UI_SKILL:
1653 i = trap_Cvar_VariableValue( "g_spSkill" );
1654 if (i < 1 || i > numSkillLevels) {
1655 i = 1;
1656 }
1657 s = skillLevels[i-1];
1658 break;
1659 case UI_BLUETEAMNAME:
1660 i = UI_TeamIndexFromName(UI_Cvar_VariableString("ui_blueTeam"));
1661 if (i >= 0 && i < uiInfo.teamCount) {
1662 s = va("%s: %s", "Blue", uiInfo.teamList[i].teamName);
1663 }
1664 break;
1665 case UI_REDTEAMNAME:
1666 i = UI_TeamIndexFromName(UI_Cvar_VariableString("ui_redTeam"));
1667 if (i >= 0 && i < uiInfo.teamCount) {
1668 s = va("%s: %s", "Red", uiInfo.teamList[i].teamName);
1669 }
1670 break;
1671 case UI_BLUETEAM1:
1672 case UI_BLUETEAM2:
1673 case UI_BLUETEAM3:
1674 case UI_BLUETEAM4:
1675 case UI_BLUETEAM5:
1676 value = trap_Cvar_VariableValue(va("ui_blueteam%i", ownerDraw-UI_BLUETEAM1 + 1));
1677 if (value <= 0) {
1678 text = "Closed";
1679 } else if (value == 1) {
1680 text = "Human";
1681 } else {
1682 value -= 2;
1683 if (value >= uiInfo.aliasCount) {
1684 value = 0;
1685 }
1686 text = uiInfo.aliasList[value].name;
1687 }
1688 s = va("%i. %s", ownerDraw-UI_BLUETEAM1 + 1, text);
1689 break;
1690 case UI_REDTEAM1:
1691 case UI_REDTEAM2:
1692 case UI_REDTEAM3:
1693 case UI_REDTEAM4:
1694 case UI_REDTEAM5:
1695 value = trap_Cvar_VariableValue(va("ui_redteam%i", ownerDraw-UI_REDTEAM1 + 1));
1696 if (value <= 0) {
1697 text = "Closed";
1698 } else if (value == 1) {
1699 text = "Human";
1700 } else {
1701 value -= 2;
1702 if (value >= uiInfo.aliasCount) {
1703 value = 0;
1704 }
1705 text = uiInfo.aliasList[value].name;
1706 }
1707 s = va("%i. %s", ownerDraw-UI_REDTEAM1 + 1, text);
1708 break;
1709 case UI_NETSOURCE:
1710 if (ui_netSource.integer < 0 || ui_netSource.integer >= numNetSources) {
1711 ui_netSource.integer = 0;
1712 }
1713 s = va("Source: %s", netSources[ui_netSource.integer]);
1714 break;
1715 case UI_NETFILTER:
1716 if (ui_serverFilterType.integer < 0 || ui_serverFilterType.integer >= numServerFilters) {
1717 ui_serverFilterType.integer = 0;
1718 }
1719 s = va("Filter: %s", serverFilters[ui_serverFilterType.integer].description );
1720 break;
1721 case UI_TIER:
1722 break;
1723 case UI_TIER_MAPNAME:
1724 break;
1725 case UI_TIER_GAMETYPE:
1726 break;
1727 case UI_ALLMAPS_SELECTION:
1728 break;
1729 case UI_OPPONENT_NAME:
1730 break;
1731 case UI_KEYBINDSTATUS:
1732 if (Display_KeyBindPending()) {
1733 s = "Waiting for new key... Press ESCAPE to cancel";
1734 } else {
1735 s = "Press ENTER or CLICK to change, Press BACKSPACE to clear";
1736 }
1737 break;
1738 case UI_SERVERREFRESHDATE:
1739 s = UI_Cvar_VariableString(va("ui_lastServerRefresh_%i", ui_netSource.integer));
1740 break;
1741 default:
1742 break;
1743 }
1744
1745 if (s) {
1746 return Text_Width(s, scale, 0);
1747 }
1748 return 0;
1749}

1788/*
1789===============
1790UI_BuildPlayerList
1791===============
1792*/
1793static void UI_BuildPlayerList( void ) {
1794 uiClientState_t cs;
1795 int n, count, team, team2, playerTeamNumber;
1796 char info[MAX_INFO_STRING];
1797
1798 trap_GetClientState( &cs );
1799 trap_GetConfigString( CS_PLAYERS + cs.clientNum, info, MAX_INFO_STRING );
1800 uiInfo.playerNumber = cs.clientNum;
1801 uiInfo.teamLeader = atoi(Info_ValueForKey(info, "tl"));
1802 team = atoi(Info_ValueForKey(info, "t"));
1803 trap_GetConfigString( CS_SERVERINFO, info, sizeof(info) );
1804 count = atoi( Info_ValueForKey( info, "sv_maxclients" ) );
1805 uiInfo.playerCount = 0;
1806 uiInfo.myTeamCount = 0;
1807 playerTeamNumber = 0;
1808 for( n = 0; n < count; n++ ) {
1809 trap_GetConfigString( CS_PLAYERS + n, info, MAX_INFO_STRING );
1810
1811 if (info[0]) {
1812 Q_strncpyz( uiInfo.playerNames[uiInfo.playerCount], Info_ValueForKey( info, "n" ), MAX_NAME_LENGTH );
1813 Q_CleanStr( uiInfo.playerNames[uiInfo.playerCount] );
1814 uiInfo.playerCount++;
1815 team2 = atoi(Info_ValueForKey(info, "t"));
1816 if (team2 == team) {
1817 Q_strncpyz( uiInfo.teamNames[uiInfo.myTeamCount], Info_ValueForKey( info, "n" ), MAX_NAME_LENGTH );
1818 Q_CleanStr( uiInfo.teamNames[uiInfo.myTeamCount] );
1819 uiInfo.teamClientNums[uiInfo.myTeamCount] = n;
1820 if (uiInfo.playerNumber == n) {
1821 playerTeamNumber = uiInfo.myTeamCount;
1822 }
1823 uiInfo.myTeamCount++;
1824 }
1825 }
1826 }
1827
1828 if (!uiInfo.teamLeader) {
1829 trap_Cvar_Set("cg_selectedPlayer", va("%d", playerTeamNumber));
1830 }
1831
1832 n = trap_Cvar_VariableValue("cg_selectedPlayer");
1833 if (n < 0 || n > uiInfo.myTeamCount) {
1834 n = 0;
1835 }
1836 if (n < uiInfo.myTeamCount) {
1837 trap_Cvar_Set("cg_selectedPlayerName", uiInfo.teamNames[n]);
1838 }
1839}

1882 if (uiInfo.uiDC.realTime > uiInfo.serverStatus.motdTime) {
1883 uiInfo.serverStatus.motdTime = uiInfo.uiDC.realTime + 10;
1884 if (uiInfo.serverStatus.motdPaintX <= rect->x + 2) {

1886 uiInfo.serverStatus.motdPaintX += Text_Width(&uiInfo.serverStatus.motd[uiInfo.serverStatus.motdOffset], scale, 1) - 1;
1887 uiInfo.serverStatus.motdOffset++;
1888 } else {
1889 uiInfo.serverStatus.motdOffset = 0;
1890 if (uiInfo.serverStatus.motdPaintX2 >= 0) {
1891 uiInfo.serverStatus.motdPaintX = uiInfo.serverStatus.motdPaintX2;
1892 } else {
1893 uiInfo.serverStatus.motdPaintX = rect->x + rect->w - 2;
1894 }
1895 uiInfo.serverStatus.motdPaintX2 = -1;
1896 }
1897 } else {
1898 //serverStatus.motdPaintX--;
1899 uiInfo.serverStatus.motdPaintX -= 2;
1900 if (uiInfo.serverStatus.motdPaintX2 >= 0) {
1901 //serverStatus.motdPaintX2--;
1902 uiInfo.serverStatus.motdPaintX2 -= 2;
1903 }
1904 }
1905 }
1906
1907 maxX = rect->x + rect->w - 2;
1908 Text_Paint_Limit(&maxX, uiInfo.serverStatus.motdPaintX, rect->y + rect->h - 3, scale, color, &uiInfo.serverStatus.motd[uiInfo.serverStatus.motdOffset], 0, 0);
1909 if (uiInfo.serverStatus.motdPaintX2 >= 0) {

1912 }
1913 if (uiInfo.serverStatus.motdOffset && maxX > 0) {
1914 // if we have an offset ( we are skipping the first part of the string ) and we fit the string

1934static void UI_DrawGLInfo(rectDef_t *rect, float scale, vec4_t color, int textStyle) {
1935 char * eptr;
1936 char buff[1024];
1937 const char *lines[64];
1938 int y, numLines, i;
1939
1940 Text_Paint(rect->x + 2, rect->y, scale, color, va("VENDOR: %s", uiInfo.uiDC.glconfig.vendor_string), 0, 30, textStyle);
1941 Text_Paint(rect->x + 2, rect->y + 15, scale, color, va("VERSION: %s: %s", uiInfo.uiDC.glconfig.version_string,uiInfo.uiDC.glconfig.renderer_string), 0, 30, textStyle);
1942 Text_Paint(rect->x + 2, rect->y + 30, scale, color, va ("PIXELFORMAT: color(%d-bits) Z(%d-bits) stencil(%d-bits)", uiInfo.uiDC.glconfig.colorBits, uiInfo.uiDC.glconfig.depthBits, uiInfo.uiDC.glconfig.stencilBits), 0, 30, textStyle);
1943
1944 // build null terminated extension strings
1945 // TTimo: https://zerowing.idsoftware.com/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=399
1946 // in TA this was not directly crashing, but displaying a nasty broken shader right in the middle
1947 // brought down the string size to 1024, there's not much that can be shown on the screen anyway
1948 Q_strncpyz(buff, uiInfo.uiDC.glconfig.extensions_string, 1024);
1949 eptr = buff;
1950 y = rect->y + 45;
1951 numLines = 0;
1952 while ( y < rect->y + rect->h && *eptr )
1953 {
1954 while ( *eptr && *eptr == ' ' )
1955 *eptr++ = '\0';
1956
1957 // track start of valid string
1958 if (*eptr && *eptr != ' ') {
1959 lines[numLines++] = eptr;
1960 }
1961
1962 while ( *eptr && *eptr != ' ' )
1963 eptr++;
1964 }
1965
1966 i = 0;
1967 while (i < numLines) {
1968 Text_Paint(rect->x + 2, y, scale, color, lines[i++], 0, 20, textStyle);
1969 if (i < numLines) {
1970 Text_Paint(rect->x + rect->w / 2, y, scale, color, lines[i++], 0, 20, textStyle);
1971 }
1972 y += 10;
1973 if (y > rect->y + rect->h - 11) {
1974 break;
1975 }
1976 }
1977
1978
1979}

2150static qboolean UI_OwnerDrawVisible(int flags) {

2153 while (flags) {
2154

2157 vis = qfalse;

2159 flags &= ~UI_SHOW_FFA;
2160 }
2161
2162 if (flags & UI_SHOW_NOTFFA) {
2163 if (trap_Cvar_VariableValue("g_gametype") == GT_FFA) {

2166 flags &= ~UI_SHOW_NOTFFA;
2167 }
2168
2169 if (flags & UI_SHOW_LEADER) {

2174 // if showing yourself

2178 }

2186 vis = qfalse;
2187 }
2188 // these need to show when this client can give orders to a player or a group
2189 }

2200 // this assumes you only put this type of display flag on something showing in the proper context
2201 if (ui_netSource.integer == UIAS_FAVORITES) {
2202 vis = qfalse;

3037static void UI_Update(const char *name) {
3038 int val = trap_Cvar_VariableValue(name);
3039
3040 if (Q_stricmp(name, "ui_SetName") == 0) {
3041 trap_Cvar_Set( "name", UI_Cvar_VariableString("ui_Name"));
3042 } else if (Q_stricmp(name, "ui_setRate") == 0) {
3043 float rate = trap_Cvar_VariableValue("rate");
3044 if (rate >= 5000) {
3045 trap_Cvar_Set("cl_maxpackets", "30");
3046 trap_Cvar_Set("cl_packetdup", "1");
3047 } else if (rate >= 4000) {
3048 trap_Cvar_Set("cl_maxpackets", "15");
3049 trap_Cvar_Set("cl_packetdup", "2"); // favor less prediction errors when there's packet loss
3050 } else {
3051 trap_Cvar_Set("cl_maxpackets", "15");
3052 trap_Cvar_Set("cl_packetdup", "1"); // favor lower bandwidth
3053 }

3543/*
3544==================
3545UI_MapCountByGameType
3546==================
3547*/
3548static int UI_MapCountByGameType(qboolean singlePlayer) {
3549 int i, c, game;
3550 c = 0;
3551 game = singlePlayer ? uiInfo.gameTypes[ui_gameType.integer].gtEnum : uiInfo.gameTypes[ui_netGameType.integer].gtEnum;
3552 if (game == GT_SINGLE_PLAYER) {
3553 game++;
3554 }
3555 if (game == GT_TEAM) {
3556 game = GT_FFA;
3557 }
3558
3559 for (i = 0; i < uiInfo.mapCount; i++) {
3560 uiInfo.mapList[i].active = qfalse;
3561 if ( uiInfo.mapList[i].typeBits & (1 << game)) {
3562 if (singlePlayer) {
3563 if (!(uiInfo.mapList[i].typeBits & (1 << GT_SINGLE_PLAYER))) {
3564 continue;
3565 }
3566 }
3567 c++;
3568 uiInfo.mapList[i].active = qtrue;
3569 }
3570 }
3571 return c;
3572}

3692/*
3693==================
3694UI_BinaryServerInsertion
3695==================
3696*/
3697static void UI_BinaryServerInsertion(int num) {
3698 int mid, offset, res, len;
3699
3700 // use binary search to insert server
3701 len = uiInfo.serverStatus.numDisplayServers;
3702 mid = len;
3703 offset = 0;
3704 res = 0;
3705 while(mid > 0) {
3706 mid = len >> 1;
3707 //
3708 res = trap_LAN_CompareServers( UI_SourceForLAN(), uiInfo.serverStatus.sortKey,
3709 uiInfo.serverStatus.sortDir, num, uiInfo.serverStatus.displayServers[offset+mid]);
3710 // if equal
3711 if (res == 0) {
3712 UI_InsertServerIntoDisplayList(num, offset+mid);
3713 return;
3714 }
3715 // if larger
3716 else if (res == 1) {
3717 offset += mid;
3718 len -= mid;
3719 }
3720 // if smaller
3721 else {
3722 len -= mid;
3723 }
3724 }
3725 if (res == 1) {
3726 offset++;
3727 }
3728 UI_InsertServerIntoDisplayList(num, offset);
3729}

3731/*

3733UI_BuildServerDisplayList
3734==================
3735*/
3736static void UI_BuildServerDisplayList(int force) {
3737 int i, count, clients, maxClients, ping, game, len, visible;
3738 char info[MAX_STRING_CHARS];
3739// qboolean startRefresh = qtrue; TTimo: unused
3740 static int numinvisible;
3741 int lanSource;
3742
3743 if (!(force || uiInfo.uiDC.realTime > uiInfo.serverStatus.nextDisplayRefresh)) {
3744 return;
3745 }
3746 // if we shouldn't reset
3747 if ( force == 2 ) {
3748 force = 0;
3749 }
3750
3751 // do motd updates here too
3752 trap_Cvar_VariableStringBuffer( "cl_motdString", uiInfo.serverStatus.motd, sizeof(uiInfo.serverStatus.motd) );
3753 len = strlen(uiInfo.serverStatus.motd);
3754 if (len == 0) {

3756 len = strlen(uiInfo.serverStatus.motd);
3757 }
3758 if (len != uiInfo.serverStatus.motdLen) {
3759 uiInfo.serverStatus.motdLen = len;
3760 uiInfo.serverStatus.motdWidth = -1;
3761 }
3762
3763 lanSource = UI_SourceForLAN();
3764
3765 if (force) {
3766 numinvisible = 0;
3767 // clear number of displayed servers
3768 uiInfo.serverStatus.numDisplayServers = 0;
3769 uiInfo.serverStatus.numPlayersOnServers = 0;
3770 // set list box index to zero
3771 Menu_SetFeederSelection(NULL, FEEDER_SERVERS, 0, NULL);
3772 // mark all servers as visible so we store ping updates for them
3773 trap_LAN_MarkServerVisible(lanSource, -1, qtrue);
3774 }
3775
3776 // get the server count (comes from the master)
3777 count = trap_LAN_GetServerCount(lanSource);
3778 if (count == -1 || (ui_netSource.integer == UIAS_LOCAL && count == 0) ) {
3779 // still waiting on a response from the master

3781 uiInfo.serverStatus.numPlayersOnServers = 0;
3782 uiInfo.serverStatus.nextDisplayRefresh = uiInfo.uiDC.realTime + 500;

3784 }
3785

3787 for (i = 0; i < count; i++) {
3788 // if we already got info for this server
3789 if (!trap_LAN_ServerIsVisible(lanSource, i)) {
3790 continue;
3791 }
3792 visible = qtrue;
3793 // get the ping for this server
3794 ping = trap_LAN_GetServerPing(lanSource, i);
3795 if (ping > 0 || ui_netSource.integer == UIAS_FAVORITES) {
3796 // Remove favorite servers so they do not appear multiple times
3797 // or appear when the cached server info was not filtered out
3798 // but the new server info is filtered out.
3799 if (ui_netSource.integer == UIAS_FAVORITES) {
3800 UI_RemoveServerFromDisplayList(i);
3801 }
3802

3804
3805 clients = atoi(Info_ValueForKey(info, "clients"));
3806
3807 if (ui_browserShowEmpty.integer == 0) {
3808 if (clients == 0) {
3809 if (ping > 0) {
3810 trap_LAN_MarkServerVisible(lanSource, i, qfalse);
3811 }
3812 continue;
3813 }
3814 }
3815
3816 if (ui_browserShowFull.integer == 0) {
3817 maxClients = atoi(Info_ValueForKey(info, "sv_maxclients"));
3818 if (clients == maxClients) {
3819 if (ping > 0) {
3820 trap_LAN_MarkServerVisible(lanSource, i, qfalse);
3821 }
3822 continue;
3823 }
3824 }
3825
3826 if (uiInfo.joinGameTypes[ui_joinGameType.integer].gtEnum != -1) {
3827 game = atoi(Info_ValueForKey(info, "gametype"));
3828 if (game != uiInfo.joinGameTypes[ui_joinGameType.integer].gtEnum) {
3829 if (ping > 0) {
3830 trap_LAN_MarkServerVisible(lanSource, i, qfalse);
3831 }
3832 continue;
3833 }
3834 }
3835
3836 if (ui_serverFilterType.integer > 0) {
3837 if (Q_stricmp(Info_ValueForKey(info, "game"), serverFilters[ui_serverFilterType.integer].basedir) != 0) {
3838 if (ping > 0) {
3839 trap_LAN_MarkServerVisible(lanSource, i, qfalse);
3840 }
3841 continue;
3842 }
3843 }
3844 // insert the server into the list
3845 UI_BinaryServerInsertion(i);
3846 // done with this server
3847 if (ping > 0) {
3848 trap_LAN_MarkServerVisible(lanSource, i, qfalse);
3849 uiInfo.serverStatus.numPlayersOnServers += clients;
3850 numinvisible++;
3851 }
3852 }
3853 }
3854
3855 uiInfo.serverStatus.refreshtime = uiInfo.uiDC.realTime;
3856
3857 // if there were no servers visible for ping updates
3858 if (!visible) {
3859// UI_StopServerRefresh();
3860// uiInfo.serverStatus.nextDisplayRefresh = 0;
3861 }
3862}

3905 info->lines[index][3] = info->lines[j][3];

3907 info->lines[j][3] = tmp2;
3908 //
3909 if ( strlen(serverStatusCvars[i].altName) ) {
3910 info->lines[index][0] = serverStatusCvars[i].altName;
3911 }
3912 index++;
3913 }

3918/*
3919==================
3920UI_GetServerStatusInfo
3921==================
3922*/
3923static int UI_GetServerStatusInfo( const char *serverAddress, serverStatusInfo_t *info ) {
3924 char *p, *score, *ping, *name;
3925 int i, len;
3926
3927 if (info) {
3928 memset(info, 0, sizeof(*info));
3929 }
3930
3931 // ignore initial unset addresses
3932 if (serverAddress && *serverAddress == '\0') {
3933 return qfalse;
3934 }
3935
3936 // reset server status request for this address
3937 if (!info) {
3938 trap_LAN_ServerStatus( serverAddress, NULL, 0);
3939 return qfalse;
3940 }
3941
3942 if ( trap_LAN_ServerStatus( serverAddress, info->text, sizeof(info->text)) ) {
3943 Q_strncpyz(info->address, serverAddress, sizeof(info->address));
3944 p = info->text;
3945 info->numLines = 0;
3946 info->lines[info->numLines][0] = "Address";
3947 info->lines[info->numLines][1] = "";
3948 info->lines[info->numLines][2] = "";
3949 info->lines[info->numLines][3] = info->address;
3950 info->numLines++;
3951 // get the cvars
3952 while (p && *p) {
3953 p = strchr(p, '\\');
3954 if (!p) break;
3955 *p++ = '\0';
3956 if (*p == '\\')
3957 break;
3958 info->lines[info->numLines][0] = p;
3959 info->lines[info->numLines][1] = "";
3960 info->lines[info->numLines][2] = "";
3961 p = strchr(p, '\\');
3962 if (!p) break;
3963 *p++ = '\0';
3964 info->lines[info->numLines][3] = p;
3965
3966 info->numLines++;
3967 if (info->numLines >= MAX_SERVERSTATUS_LINES)
3968 break;
3969 }
3970 // get the player list
3971 if (info->numLines < MAX_SERVERSTATUS_LINES-3) {
3972 // empty line
3973 info->lines[info->numLines][0] = "";
3974 info->lines[info->numLines][1] = "";
3975 info->lines[info->numLines][2] = "";
3976 info->lines[info->numLines][3] = "";
3977 info->numLines++;
3978 // header
3979 info->lines[info->numLines][0] = "num";
3980 info->lines[info->numLines][1] = "score";
3981 info->lines[info->numLines][2] = "ping";
3982 info->lines[info->numLines][3] = "name";
3983 info->numLines++;
3984 // parse players
3985 i = 0;
3986 len = 0;
3987 while (p && *p) {
3988 if (*p == '\\')
3989 *p++ = '\0';
3990 score = p;
3991 p = strchr(p, ' ');
3992 if (!p)
3993 break;
3994 *p++ = '\0';
3995 ping = p;
3996 p = strchr(p, ' ');
3997 if (!p)
3998 break;
3999 *p++ = '\0';
4000 name = p;
4001 Com_sprintf(&info->pings[len], sizeof(info->pings)-len, "%d", i);
4002 info->lines[info->numLines][0] = &info->pings[len];
4003 len += strlen(&info->pings[len]) + 1;
4004 info->lines[info->numLines][1] = score;
4005 info->lines[info->numLines][2] = ping;
4006 info->lines[info->numLines][3] = name;
4007 info->numLines++;
4008 if (info->numLines >= MAX_SERVERSTATUS_LINES)
4009 break;
4010 p = strchr(p, '\\');
4011 if (!p)
4012 break;
4013 *p++ = '\0';
4014 //
4015 i++;
4016 }
4017 }
4018 UI_SortServerStatusInfo( info );
4019 return qtrue;
4020 }
4021 return qfalse;
4022}

4024/*
4025==================
4026stristr
4027==================
4028*/
4029static char *stristr(char *str, char *charset) {
4030 int i;
4031
4032 while(*str) {
4033 for (i = 0; charset[i] && str[i]; i++) {
4034 if (toupper(charset[i]) != toupper(str[i])) break;
4035 }
4036 if (!charset[i]) return str;
4037 str++;
4038 }
4039 return NULL;
4040}

4537static qboolean Team_Parse(char **p) {
4538 char *token;
4539 const char *tempStr;
4540 int i;
4541
4542 token = COM_ParseExt(p, qtrue);
4543
4544 if (token[0] != '{') {
4545 return qfalse;
4546 }
4547
4548 while ( 1 ) {
4549
4550 token = COM_ParseExt(p, qtrue);
4551
4552 if (Q_stricmp(token, "}") == 0) {
4553 return qtrue;
4554 }
4555
4556 if (!token[0]) {
4557 return qfalse;
4558 }
4559
4560 if (token[0] == '{') {
4561 if (uiInfo.teamCount == MAX_TEAMS) {
4562 uiInfo.teamCount--;
4563 Com_Printf("Too many teams, last team replaced!\n");
4564 }
4565
4566 // seven tokens per line, team name and icon, and 5 team member names
4567 if (!String_Parse(p, &uiInfo.teamList[uiInfo.teamCount].teamName) || !String_Parse(p, &tempStr)) {
4568 return qfalse;
4569 }
4570
4571
4572 uiInfo.teamList[uiInfo.teamCount].imageName = tempStr;
4573 uiInfo.teamList[uiInfo.teamCount].teamIcon = trap_R_RegisterShaderNoMip(uiInfo.teamList[uiInfo.teamCount].imageName);
4574 uiInfo.teamList[uiInfo.teamCount].teamIcon_Metal = trap_R_RegisterShaderNoMip(va("%s_metal",uiInfo.teamList[uiInfo.teamCount].imageName));
4575 uiInfo.teamList[uiInfo.teamCount].teamIcon_Name = trap_R_RegisterShaderNoMip(va("%s_name", uiInfo.teamList[uiInfo.teamCount].imageName));
4576
4577 uiInfo.teamList[uiInfo.teamCount].cinematic = -1;
4578
4579 for (i = 0; i < TEAM_MEMBERS; i++) {
4580 uiInfo.teamList[uiInfo.teamCount].teamMembers[i] = NULL;
4581 if (!String_Parse(p, &uiInfo.teamList[uiInfo.teamCount].teamMembers[i])) {
4582 return qfalse;
4583 }
4584 }
4585
4586 Com_Printf("Loaded team %s with team icon %s.\n", uiInfo.teamList[uiInfo.teamCount].teamName, tempStr);
4587 uiInfo.teamCount++;
4588
4589 token = COM_ParseExt(p, qtrue);
4590 if (token[0] != '}') {
4591 return qfalse;
4592 }
4593 }
4594 }
4595
4596 return qfalse;
4597}

4610 while ( 1 ) {

4707static void UI_ParseTeamInfo(const char *teamFile) {

4877static void UI_ParseGameInfo(const char *teamFile) {
4878 char *token;
4879 char *p;
4880 char *buff = NULL;
4881 //int mode = 0; TTimo: unused
4882
4883 buff = GetMenuBuffer(teamFile);
4884 if (!buff) {
4885 return;
4886 }
4887
4888 p = buff;
4889
4890 while ( 1 ) {
4891 token = COM_ParseExt( &p, qtrue );
4892 if (!token[0] || token[0] == '}') {
4893 break;
4894 }
4895
4896 if ( Q_stricmp( token, "}" ) == 0 ) {
4897 break;
4898 }
4899
4900 if (Q_stricmp(token, "gametypes") == 0) {
4901
4902 if (GameType_Parse(&p, qfalse)) {
4903 continue;
4904 } else {
4905 break;
4906 }
4907 }
4908
4909 if (Q_stricmp(token, "joingametypes") == 0) {
4910
4911 if (GameType_Parse(&p, qtrue)) {
4912 continue;
4913 } else {
4914 break;
4915 }
4916 }
4917
4918 if (Q_stricmp(token, "maps") == 0) {
4919 // start a new menu
4920 MapList_Parse(&p);
4921 }
4922
4923 }
4924}

5363static void UI_ReadableSize ( char *buf, int bufsize, int value )
5364{
5365 if (value > 1024*1024*1024 ) { // gigs
5366 Com_sprintf( buf, bufsize, "%d", value / (1024*1024*1024) );
5367 Com_sprintf( buf+strlen(buf), bufsize-strlen(buf), ".%02d GB",
5368 (value % (1024*1024*1024))*100 / (1024*1024*1024) );
5369 } else if (value > 1024*1024 ) { // megs
5370 Com_sprintf( buf, bufsize, "%d", value / (1024*1024) );
5371 Com_sprintf( buf+strlen(buf), bufsize-strlen(buf), ".%02d MB",
5372 (value % (1024*1024))*100 / (1024*1024) );
5373 } else if (value > 1024 ) { // kilos
5374 Com_sprintf( buf, bufsize, "%d KB", value / 1024 );
5375 } else { // bytes
5376 Com_sprintf( buf, bufsize, "%d bytes", value );
5377 }
5378}

5381static void UI_PrintTime ( char *buf, int bufsize, int time ) {
5382 time /= 1000; // change to seconds
5383
5384 if (time > 3600) { // in the hours range
5385 Com_sprintf( buf, bufsize, "%d hr %d min", time / 3600, (time % 3600) / 60 );
5386 } else if (time > 60) { // mins
5387 Com_sprintf( buf, bufsize, "%d min %d sec", time / 60, time % 60 );
5388 } else { // secs
5389 Com_sprintf( buf, bufsize, "%d sec", time );
5390 }
5391}

5397
5398void Text_PaintCenter_AutoWrapped(float x, float y, float xmax, float ystep, float scale, vec4_t color, const char *str, float adjust) {
5399 int width;
5400 char *s1,*s2,*s3;
5401 char c_bcp;
5402 char buf[1024];
5403
5404 if (!str || str[0]=='\0')
5405 return;
5406
5407 Q_strncpyz(buf, str, sizeof(buf));
5408 s1 = s2 = s3 = buf;
5409
5410 while (1) {
5411 do {
5412 s3++;
5413 } while (*s3!=' ' && *s3!='\0');
5414 c_bcp = *s3;
5415 *s3 = '\0';
5416 width = Text_Width(s1, scale, 0);
5417 *s3 = c_bcp;
5418 if (width > xmax) {
5419 if (s1==s2)
5420 {
5421 // fuck, don't have a clean cut, we'll overflow
5422 s2 = s3;
5423 }
5424 *s2 = '\0';
5425 Text_PaintCenter(x, y, scale, color, s1, adjust);
5426 y += ystep;
5427 if (c_bcp == '\0')
5428 {
5429 // that was the last word
5430 // we could start a new loop, but that wouldn't be much use
5431 // even if the word is too long, we would overflow it (see above)
5432 // so just print it now if needed
5433 s2++;
5434 if (*s2 != '\0') // if we are printing an overflowing line we have s2 == s3
5435 Text_PaintCenter(x, y, scale, color, s2, adjust);
5436 break;
5437 }
5438 s2++;
5439 s1 = s2;
5440 s3 = s2;
5441 }
5442 else
5443 {
5444 s2 = s3;
5445 if (c_bcp == '\0') // we reached the end
5446 {
5447 Text_PaintCenter(x, y, scale, color, s1, adjust);
5448 break;
5449 }
5450 }
5451 }
5452}

5455 static char dlText[] = "Downloading:";
5456 static char etaText[] = "Estimated time left:";
5457 static char xferText[] = "Transfer rate:";
5458
5459 int downloadSize, downloadCount, downloadTime;
5460 char dlSizeBuf[64], totalSizeBuf[64], xferRateBuf[64], dlTimeBuf[64];
5461 int xferRate;
5462 int leftWidth;
5463 const char *s;
5464
5465 downloadSize = trap_Cvar_VariableValue( "cl_downloadSize" );
5466 downloadCount = trap_Cvar_VariableValue( "cl_downloadCount" );
5467 downloadTime = trap_Cvar_VariableValue( "cl_downloadTime" );
5468
5469 leftWidth = 320;
5470
5471 UI_SetColor(colorWhite);
5472 Text_PaintCenter(centerPoint, yStart + 112, scale, colorWhite, dlText, 0);
5473 Text_PaintCenter(centerPoint, yStart + 192, scale, colorWhite, etaText, 0);
5474 Text_PaintCenter(centerPoint, yStart + 248, scale, colorWhite, xferText, 0);
5475
5476 if (downloadSize > 0) {
5477 s = va( "%s (%d%%)", downloadName,
5478 (int)( (float)downloadCount * 100.0f / downloadSize ) );
5479 } else {
5480 s = downloadName;
5481 }
5482
5483 Text_PaintCenter(centerPoint, yStart+136, scale, colorWhite, s, 0);
5484
5485 UI_ReadableSize( dlSizeBuf, sizeof dlSizeBuf, downloadCount );
5486 UI_ReadableSize( totalSizeBuf, sizeof totalSizeBuf, downloadSize );
5487
5488 if (downloadCount < 4096 || !downloadTime) {
5489 Text_PaintCenter(leftWidth, yStart+216, scale, colorWhite, "estimating", 0);
5490 Text_PaintCenter(leftWidth, yStart+160, scale, colorWhite, va("(%s of %s copied)", dlSizeBuf, totalSizeBuf), 0);
5491 } else {
5492 if ((uiInfo.uiDC.realTime - downloadTime) / 1000) {
5493 xferRate = downloadCount / ((uiInfo.uiDC.realTime - downloadTime) / 1000);
5494 } else {
5495 xferRate = 0;
5496 }
5497 UI_ReadableSize( xferRateBuf, sizeof xferRateBuf, xferRate );
5498
5499 // Extrapolate estimated completion time
5500 if (downloadSize && xferRate) {
5501 int n = downloadSize / xferRate; // estimated time for entire d/l in secs
5502
5503 // We do it in K (/1024) because we'd overflow around 4MB
5504 UI_PrintTime ( dlTimeBuf, sizeof dlTimeBuf,
5505 (n - (((downloadCount/1024) * n) / (downloadSize/1024))) * 1000);
5506
5507 Text_PaintCenter(leftWidth, yStart+216, scale, colorWhite, dlTimeBuf, 0);
5508 Text_PaintCenter(leftWidth, yStart+160, scale, colorWhite, va("(%s of %s copied)", dlSizeBuf, totalSizeBuf), 0);
5509 } else {
5510 Text_PaintCenter(leftWidth, yStart+216, scale, colorWhite, "estimating", 0);
5511 if (downloadSize) {
5512 Text_PaintCenter(leftWidth, yStart+160, scale, colorWhite, va("(%s of %s copied)", dlSizeBuf, totalSizeBuf), 0);
5513 } else {
5514 Text_PaintCenter(leftWidth, yStart+160, scale, colorWhite, va("(%s copied)", dlSizeBuf), 0);
5515 }
5516 }
5517
5518 if (xferRate) {
5519 Text_PaintCenter(leftWidth, yStart+272, scale, colorWhite, va("%s/Sec", xferRateBuf), 0);
5520 }
5521 }
5522}

5524/*
5525========================
5526UI_DrawConnectScreen
5527
5528This will also be overlaid on the cgame info screen during loading
5529to prevent it from blinking away too rapidly on local or lan games.
5530========================
5531*/
5532void UI_DrawConnectScreen( qboolean overlay ) {
5533 char *s;
5534 uiClientState_t cstate;
5535 char info[MAX_INFO_VALUE];
5536 char text[256];
5537 float centerPoint, yStart, scale;
5538
5539 menuDef_t *menu = Menus_FindByName("Connect");
5540
5541
5542 if ( !overlay && menu ) {
5543 Menu_Paint(menu, qtrue);
5544 }
5545
5546 if (!overlay) {
5547 centerPoint = 320;
5548 yStart = 130;
5549 scale = 0.5f;
5550 } else {
5551 return;
5552 }
5553
5554 // see what information we should display
5555 trap_GetClientState( &cstate );
5556
5557 info[0] = '\0';
5558 if( trap_GetConfigString( CS_SERVERINFO, info, sizeof(info) ) ) {
5559 Text_PaintCenter(centerPoint, yStart, scale, colorWhite, va( "Loading %s", Info_ValueForKey( info, "mapname" )), 0);
5560 }
5561
5562 if (!Q_stricmp(cstate.servername,"localhost")) {
5563 Text_PaintCenter(centerPoint, yStart + 48, scale, colorWhite, "Starting up...", ITEM_TEXTSTYLE_SHADOWEDMORE);
5564 } else {
5565 Com_sprintf(text, sizeof(text), "Connecting to %s", cstate.servername);
5566 Text_PaintCenter(centerPoint, yStart + 48, scale, colorWhite,text , ITEM_TEXTSTYLE_SHADOWEDMORE);
5567 }
5568
5569 // display global MOTD at bottom
5570 Text_PaintCenter(centerPoint, 600, scale, colorWhite, Info_ValueForKey( cstate.updateInfoString, "motd" ), 0);
5571 // print any server info (server full, bad version, etc)
5572 if ( cstate.connState < CA_CONNECTED ) {
5573 Text_PaintCenter_AutoWrapped(centerPoint, yStart + 176, 630, 20, scale, colorWhite, cstate.messageString, 0);
5574 }
5575
5576 if ( lastConnState > cstate.connState ) {
5577 lastLoadingText[0] = '\0';
5578 }
5579 lastConnState = cstate.connState;
5580
5581 switch ( cstate.connState ) {
5582 case CA_CONNECTING:
5583 s = va("Awaiting connection...%i", cstate.connectPacketCount);
5584 break;
5585 case CA_CHALLENGING:
5586 s = va("Awaiting challenge...%i", cstate.connectPacketCount);
5587 break;
5588 case CA_CONNECTED: {
5589 char downloadName[MAX_INFO_VALUE];
5590
5591 trap_Cvar_VariableStringBuffer( "cl_downloadName", downloadName, sizeof(downloadName) );
5592 if (*downloadName) {
5593 UI_DisplayDownloadInfo( downloadName, centerPoint, yStart, scale );
5594 return;
5595 }
5596 }
5597 s = "Awaiting gamestate...";
5598 break;
5599 case CA_LOADING:
5600 return;
5601 case CA_PRIMED:
5602 return;
5603 default:
5604 return;
5605 }
5606
5607
5608 if (Q_stricmp(cstate.servername,"localhost")) {
5609 Text_PaintCenter(centerPoint, yStart + 80, scale, colorWhite, s, 0);
5610 }
5611
5612 // password required / connection rejected information goes here
5613}

5953/*
5954=================
5955UI_DoServerRefresh
5956=================
5957*/
5958static void UI_DoServerRefresh( void )
5959{
5960 qboolean wait = qfalse;
5961
5962 if (!uiInfo.serverStatus.refreshActive) {
5963 return;
5964 }
5965 if (ui_netSource.integer != UIAS_FAVORITES) {
5966 if (ui_netSource.integer == UIAS_LOCAL) {
5967 if (!trap_LAN_GetServerCount(AS_LOCAL)) {
5968 wait = qtrue;
5969 }
5970 } else {
5971 if (trap_LAN_GetServerCount(AS_GLOBAL) < 0) {
5972 wait = qtrue;
5973 }
5974 }
5975 }
5976
5977 if (uiInfo.uiDC.realTime < uiInfo.serverStatus.refreshtime) {
5978 if (wait) {
5979 return;
5980 }
5981 }
5982
5983 // if still trying to retrieve pings
5984 if (trap_LAN_UpdateVisiblePings(UI_SourceForLAN())) {
5985 uiInfo.serverStatus.refreshtime = uiInfo.uiDC.realTime + 1000;
5986 } else if (!wait) {
5987 // get the last servers in the list
5988 UI_BuildServerDisplayList(2);
5989 // stop the refresh
5990 UI_StopServerRefresh();
5991 } else if ( ui_netSource.integer == UIAS_LOCAL ) {
5992 // no local servers found, check again
5993 trap_Cmd_ExecuteText( EXEC_NOW, "localservers\n" );
5994 uiInfo.serverStatus.refreshtime = uiInfo.uiDC.realTime + 5000;
5995 }
5996 //
5997 UI_BuildServerDisplayList(qfalse);
5998}

6000/*
6001=================
6002UI_StartServerRefresh
6003=================
6004*/
6005static void UI_StartServerRefresh(qboolean full, qboolean force)
6006{
6007 char *ptr;
6008 int lanSource;
6009 qtime_t q;
6010
6011 // This function is called with force=qfalse when server browser menu opens or net source changes.
6012 // Automatically update local and favorite servers.
6013 // Only auto update master server list if there is no server info cache.
6014 if ( !force && ( ui_netSource.integer >= UIAS_GLOBAL0 && ui_netSource.integer <= UIAS_GLOBAL5 ) ) {
6015 if ( trap_LAN_GetServerCount( UI_SourceForLAN() ) > 0 ) {
6016 return; // have cached list
6017 }
6018 }
6019
6020 trap_RealTime(&q);
6021 trap_Cvar_Set( va("ui_lastServerRefresh_%i", ui_netSource.integer), va("%s-%i, %i at %i:%i", MonthAbbrev[q.tm_mon],q.tm_mday, 1900+q.tm_year,q.tm_hour,q.tm_min));
6022
6023 if (!full) {
6024 UI_UpdatePendingPings();
6025 return;
6026 }
6027
6028 uiInfo.serverStatus.refreshActive = qtrue;
6029 uiInfo.serverStatus.nextDisplayRefresh = uiInfo.uiDC.realTime + 1000;
6030 // clear number of displayed servers
6031 uiInfo.serverStatus.numDisplayServers = 0;
6032 uiInfo.serverStatus.numPlayersOnServers = 0;
6033
6034 lanSource = UI_SourceForLAN();
6035 // mark all servers as visible so we store ping updates for them
6036 trap_LAN_MarkServerVisible(lanSource, -1, qtrue);
6037 // reset all the pings
6038 trap_LAN_ResetPings(lanSource);
6039 //
6040 if( ui_netSource.integer == UIAS_LOCAL ) {
6041 trap_Cmd_ExecuteText( EXEC_NOW, "localservers\n" );
6042 uiInfo.serverStatus.refreshtime = uiInfo.uiDC.realTime + 5000;
6043 return;
6044 }
6045
6046 uiInfo.serverStatus.refreshtime = uiInfo.uiDC.realTime + 5000;
6047 if( ui_netSource.integer >= UIAS_GLOBAL0 && ui_netSource.integer <= UIAS_GLOBAL5 ) {
6048
6049 ptr = UI_Cvar_VariableString("debug_protocol");
6050 if (strlen(ptr)) {
6051 trap_Cmd_ExecuteText( EXEC_NOW, va( "globalservers %d %s full empty\n", ui_netSource.integer - UIAS_GLOBAL0, ptr ) );
6052 }
6053 else {
6054 trap_Cmd_ExecuteText( EXEC_NOW, va( "globalservers %d %d full empty\n", ui_netSource.integer - UIAS_GLOBAL0, (int)trap_Cvar_VariableValue( "protocol" ) ) );
6055 }
6056 }
6057}
